node.text: It was a beautiful day and I’m in love with my new daughter-in-law. Check out this video shot and produced by Stephen Norregaard. See the full wide format version here: https://vimeo.com/308998543

node.text: I put together a whole set of before and after pics of The Madison kitchen. It may be hard to figure out but suffice it to say we took out some walls and decided the location of the 50’s era handicapped bath was maybe a better spot for the kitchen….once we switched out a set of doors for a set of windows.  But my question has always remained: why French doors in a bathroom? but I digress. Cabinetry by @stofferhomecabinetry Lighting and hardware from @rejuvenation Quartzite from @ariastonegallery plumbing fixtures from @kohler. Remodeling by @kenowabuilders Photography by @stofferphotographyinteriors

node.text: This in real life is a very happy sight for me. There is something about store fronts in historic buildings in old walkable neighborhoods that gets my creative juices flowing. Our flower arch @stofferhome was inspired by the flower festival in London where all the storefronts outdo each other in their spectacular displays of vibrant flower arches.  This is our rendition and I feel like a proud mother. If you come and visit us, it’s a beautiful background for a family picture to remember your time in Pure Michigan. 🌲🌊. And while you’re here, enjoy one of the best espresso drinks of your life (not kidding) @thebradburycafe inside of @stofferhome
